# PLACEHOLDER — Core image Python wheelhouse not yet populated.
#
# SCOPE: This wheelhouse contains ONLY core image build/runtime Python
# dependencies needed for the base appliance (UI, agent, inference proxy,
# tool firewall, etc.). Diffusion runtime wheels (~5 GB) are NOT checked
# into the repo — they are acquired on demand by the diffusion installer
# using committed backend-specific manifests and lockfiles under
# files/scripts/diffusion-runtime-manifest.yaml.
#
# This file must contain real SHA256 checksums before HERMETIC_BUILD=true
# can succeed. To populate:
#
#   1. Create per-service requirements.lock files with hashes:
#      pip-compile --generate-hashes -o services/<svc>/requirements.lock services/<svc>/pyproject.toml
#
#   2. Build the wheelhouse:
#      scripts/refresh-wheels.sh
#
#   3. Commit vendor/wheels/ and the updated lockfiles.
#
# Without a populated wheelhouse, the build falls back to online pip install
# (non-hermetic mode). CI with HERMETIC_BUILD=true will fail, which is the
# intended behavior — hermetic builds require all dependencies to be vendored.
